  "prompt": "What was the story between Michael and Diana Ross? Michael seemed to love her all his life, why weren't they together?",
  "response": "Michael Jackson and Diana Ross had a close, complex relationship that was more like that of a mentor and prot\u00e9g\u00e9, or an aunt-like figure and her nephew, rather than a romantic one. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Diana Ross was like a second mother to Michael Jackson. She was friends with the Jackson family and took a special interest in Michael's career from a young age.\n\n2. When the Jackson 5 first became famous, Diana Ross was already an established star. She helped introduce the group to Motown Records and was instrumental in their early success.\n\n3. Michael greatly admired and respected Diana Ross. He looked up to her as a musical icon and mentor, not as a potential romantic partner.\n\n4. There were rumors and speculation about their relationship, but these were never romantic. Their bond was more familial and professional.\n\n5. Diana Ross was supportive of Michael throughout his career and was considered a close family friend.\n\n6. Michael even dedicated his album \"Farewell My Summer Love\" to Diana Ross in 1984.\n\nWhile Michael loved Diana Ross, it was a deep, platonic love of admiration and respect, not a romantic love. They maintained a close friendship throughout Michael's life, with Diana Ross being a supportive figure in his career and personal life.",
